Here’s the updated HTML code that waits for confirmation after joining the channel before sending the `PRIVMSG #bots :.topbeans` command to fetch the beans score. This ensures the bot only sends the message once it's fully joined the channel.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Beans Score Dashboard</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            color: #333;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            height: 100vh;
            margin: 0;
        }
        #dashboard {
            background: #fff;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        #output {
            margin-top: 20px;
            padding: 10px;
            background: #eaeaea;
            border-radius: 5px;
            overflow-wrap: break-word;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="dashboard">
        <h1>Beans Score Dashboard</h1>
        <button id="fetchBeans">Get Beans Score</button>
        <div id="output"></div>
    </div>

    <script>
        const serverUrl = 'wss://irc.h4ks.com:8097';
        const channel = '#bots';
        const randomNumber = Math.floor(Math.random() * 1000); // Generate a random number
        const nick = `_robot_bean_score_fetcher_${randomNumber}`; // Nickname format
        let isJoined = false; // Flag to indicate if we have joined the channel

        const ws = new WebSocket(serverUrl);
        ws.onopen = () => {
            console.log("Connected to the server");

            // Send the NICK and USER commands
            ws.send(`NICK ${nick}`);
            ws.send(`USER ${nick} 0 * :${nick}`);
            ws.send(`PONG ${serverUrl}`);

            // Join the channel
            ws.send(`JOIN ${channel}`);
        };

        ws.onmessage = (event) => {
            const message = event.data;

            // Check for confirmation that we have joined the channel
            if (message.includes(`:${nick} JOIN ${channel}`)) {
                isJoined = true;
                console.log("Joined the channel, sending command...");
                ws.send(`PRIVMSG ${channel} :.topbeans`); // Send the command to fetch beans score
            }

            // Check for .topbeans command response from _cloudbot
            if (message.includes('_cloudbot') && message.includes('Beans:')) {
                displayOutput(message);
                leaveChannel();
            }
        };

        function displayOutput(message) {
            document.getElementById('output').innerText = message;
        }

        function leaveChannel() {
            ws.send(`PART ${channel}`);
            ws.send(`QUIT :Disconnecting`);
            setTimeout(() => {
                ws.close();
            }, 1000);
        }

        document.getElementById('fetchBeans').onclick = () => {
            if (!isJoined) {
                console.log("Joining the channel and will fetch beans score...");
            } else {
                ws.send(`PRIVMSG ${channel} :.topbeans`); // Send command if already joined
            }
        };
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation of Changes:
1. **Joining Confirmation**: The code now checks for a message that confirms the bot has successfully joined the channel. This is detected using a condition that looks for the special join message format from the IRC server.
2. **Immediate Command Sending**: Once the bot has joined the channel, it immediately sends the `PRIVMSG #bots :.topbeans` command to fetch the beans score.
3. **Fetch Beans Button**: A button click now checks if the bot has joined before trying to send any command. If it hasn't joined yet, it logs that it will fetch the beans score after joining.

### How to Use:
- Save the code as an HTML file (e.g., `beans_score_dashboard.html`).
- Open the file in a WebSocket compatible web browser.
- Click the "Get Beans Score" button to initiate the process. The bot will join the channel and fetch the beans score automatically.

### Note:
Ensure you have permission to connect to the IRC server and execute commands there. Adjust any necessary IRCHost settings as needed based on server specifications.

